<%- include('../partials/header') %>

<div class="text-center mb-4">
  <img src="/images/Flag-Colombia.webp" alt="Flag of Colombia" style="height: 80px;">
  <h1 class="mt-2"><%=title%></h1>
  <p>A few things about my home country.</p>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <img src="/images/bogota.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Bogotá, Colombia" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: cover;">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h4 class="card-title">Bogotá</h4>
    <p class="card-text">Bogotá is the capital of Colombia and sits at 8,600 feet above sea level in the Andes mountains, making it one of the highest capital cities in the world. More than 8 million people live there. It is the political, economic, and cultural center of the country. The city is known for its street art scene, the Museo del Oro which holds one of the largest collections of pre-Hispanic gold in the world, and a food scene that has grown a lot in recent years. The altitude catches a lot of visitors off guard on the first day.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <img src="/images/beach_colombia_bonita.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Colombian beach" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: cover;">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h4 class="card-title">Two Coasts</h4>
    <p class="card-text">Colombia is the only country in South America with coastline on both the Pacific Ocean and the Caribbean Sea. The Caribbean side has warmer, calmer water and popular destinations like Cartagena, Santa Marta, and the islands of San Andrés. The Pacific coast is harder to reach but worth it. Humpback whales travel there every year to give birth in the waters off towns like Nuquí. The two coasts feel like completely different countries.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <img src="/images/rel-colombia-large-map.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="Map of Colombia" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: cover;">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h4 class="card-title">Biodiversity</h4>
    <p class="card-text">Colombia has more bird species recorded than any other country on earth, over 1,900. It also ranks near the top globally for plants, amphibians, butterflies, and freshwater fish. The reason comes down to geography. The country has three separate Andean mountain ranges, the Amazon rainforest in the south, cloud forests, high altitude wetlands called páramos, and two ocean coasts. That many different ecosystems packed into one place produces an extraordinary amount of life.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
